3️⃣ Explanation of Each Flask Tool
request
📌 Definition
request is used to get data from client request.

Example in your code:
username = request.form.get("username")

Meaning:
request	--access request data
form---	form data
get()--	retrieve value

Example request data:
username=admin
password=1234

....................................................................................................
redirect
📌 Definition
redirect() sends the user to another page.

Example:
return redirect(url_for("welcome"))

Meaning:
login success
      ↓
redirect
      ↓
/welcome page

........................................................................................................
url_for
📌 Definition
url_for() generates URL using function name.

Example:
url_for("welcome")

Output:
/welcome

Why developers use it:
✔ avoids hardcoding URLs
✔ easier to manage routes
.................................................................................................
session
📌 Definition
session stores user data temporarily in browser cookies.

Example in your code:
session["user"] = username

Meaning:
session = {
   "user": "admin"
}

Later:
if "user" in session
So user stays logged in.

................................................................................................
Response
📌 Definition
Response sends custom HTTP response.

Example:
return Response("Invalid credentials", mimetype="text/plain")

Meaning:
Status → 200
Content → Invalid credentials
Type → text/plain

